<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-034-133 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 539 587</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  Oct 14 1991 n442 p6(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Claris' new agenda: look for partners.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Clancy, Heather.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Claris Corp looks for partners with which to develop softwareproducts now that the reorganization of its executive staff iscomplete.andP;  CEO Dan Eilers, in the head office since mid-Mar 1991,says the company seeks creative partnerships with vendors andresearch institutions.andP;  The company's first alliance should beannounced in 1992.andP;  The software publisher is at work on someproducts for Apple, its parent company.andP;  Products exchangedbetween the two companies include the Extend file translator andHypercard program development software.andP;  Claris is not presentlyworking with any other software developer.andP;  Claris' strategy offorming partnerships is seen as the way of the future within thecomputer industry and as a method nearly perfected by Apple.andO;Apple realized early on that by forming partnerships, it would nothave to invent everything on its own.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Claris Corp. (Product development).andO;Topic:     Management StyleProduct DevelopmentCooperative AgreementSoftware packages.andO;Person:    Eilers, Dan (Management).andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>